  "title": "Introduction to Body Temperature Regulation",
  "lessonText": "This module introduces the fundamental concepts of body temperature regulation.",
  "data": {
    "content": "### Key Concepts\n- Body temperature is vital for metabolic processes.\n- Regulation occurs through the hypothalamus.\n- Normal range is typically around 36.1°C to 37.2°C.\n- Factors affecting temperature include environment, activity, and health status."
  }
